(Tip: Click the blue number of Files at top-left to check the contents of this upload and see that your language is really there.)

One of my all-time favourite action films, partly because of the plane which I thought was a DC-10 until I discovered that it is the almost identical Lockhead Tristar.
(For planespotters: The huge DC-10 had the third engine mounted straight through the tail fin. The Tristar had only the inlet opening to the engine in front of the fin.)

Widescreen DVDrip XviD 2-pass 720x288, really great stereo sound AC3.
Burn tested, runs well in both my standalone DivX players.

(This is an improved rip of my own upload from May 2008, which had a resolution of only 608x256p and no subtitles.)
